---
export const prerender = true;
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="process" miscTitle="process" showAnnouncement={false}>
  <article class="doc">
    <header class="doc__head">
      <p class="doc__kicker">// case study &middot; graphic design</p>
      <h1 class="doc__title">the process.</h1>
      <p class="doc__lede">
        The base ingredients &mdash; colour and type &mdash; and how they carry the aesthetic
        across the neutral pages and the themed rooms.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="sec">
      <p class="sec__num">01</p>
      <h2 class="sec__h">colour</h2>

      <div class="swatches">
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #fdfcf9; border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.14)"></span>#fdfcf9 cream base</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #14131a"></span>#14131a ink</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #5061b9"></span>#5061b9 slate-violet</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #ffee00; border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.14)"></span>#ffee00 tape yellow</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #0d0c13"></span>#0d0c13 cinema</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #ff4da6"></span>#ff4da6 psg pink</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #fd7ac0"></span>#fd7ac0 nso magenta</div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="sec__sub">how it carries the aesthetic</h3>
      <p>
        The cream base and slate-violet accent do the calming work. They keep the neutral pages
        gallery-quiet so the character illustrations and product photography sit at the top of
        the visual hierarchy. The site is a catalog for a merch project, and a catalog's job is
        to disappear around the objects it holds.
      </p>
      <p>
        The tape yellow is the punch. It only appears at chip scale &mdash; sold-out ribbons,
        sticky headers, hero accents &mdash; so it snaps without competing with anything.
        Anywhere it fills more than a small badge it gets pulled back.
      </p>
      <p>
        The dark cinema pair takes over the graphic-design section. Near-black behind
        illustration reads as a lit stage, not a light box, and swapping the room's whole
        ground colour is the clearest signal that the visual rules just changed. The neutral
        pages remain cream on either side.
      </p>
      <p>
        The two pinks belong to the themed rooms and stay there. PSG pink runs the Panty &amp;
        Stocking pastiche; NSO magenta runs the Needy Streamer Overload homage. Each pink is
        loud enough to define the atmosphere of its room, and each is confined to that room so
        the neutral pages never inherit the noise.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="sec">
      <p class="sec__num">02</p>
      <h2 class="sec__h">typography</h2>

      <div class="grid grid--2">
        <div class="face">
          <p class="face__name">Apex Mk3</p>
          <p class="face__sample" style="font-family: 'Apex Mk3', monospace;">.contact</p>
          <p class="face__role">Mono. Titles, labels, nav.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="face">
          <p class="face__name">Branding Pro</p>
          <p class="face__sample" style="font-family: 'Branding Pro', sans-serif;">Body copy &mdash; running text.</p>
          <p class="face__role">Sans. Body copy.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="face">
          <p class="face__name">Beam Visionary</p>
          <p class="face__sample" style="font-family: 'Beam Visionary', cursive; font-style: italic;">from the desk.</p>
          <p class="face__role">Script italic. Eyebrows, one per section.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="face">
          <p class="face__name">NSO CRT</p>
          <p class="face__sample" style="font-family: 'NSO CRT', monospace; letter-spacing: 0.06em;">SIGNAL &gt; NO SYNC</p>
          <p class="face__role">Pixel bitmap. NSO themed room only.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="sec__sub">how it carries the aesthetic</h3>
      <p>
        The Apex Mk3 monospace on titles and labels makes the site feel tabular and considered.
        Product names, prices, section numbers, and timestamps are all short strings, and short
        strings in a mono face read as data rather than decoration. That matches the catalog
        idea &mdash; every entry is a record, not a paragraph.
      </p>
      <p>
        Branding Pro carries the running text underneath. It's a warm, wide sans that doesn't
        argue with the mono headers, so the page stays legible when the copy gets long. The two
        faces work together because they don't try to do the same job.
      </p>
      <p>
        Beam Visionary shows up once per section, usually as an eyebrow. It's a single stroke of
        handwriting in an otherwise-mechanical system, and it exists to keep the site from
        reading as pure infrastructure. One line of a person, then back to the terminal.
      </p>
      <p>
        Each themed room gets its own dedicated face. NSO CRT drives the Needy Streamer Overload
        homage; the PSG theme leans into a heavier candy-halftone display face. Changing the
        whole typeface is the fastest way to signal a themed room without spelling it out
        anywhere else on the page.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="sec sec--cta">
      <p class="sec__cta-kicker">// next</p>
      <h2 class="sec__cta-h">how it ships &rarr;</h2>
      <p>
        The whole storefront runs on a serverless AWS stack.
        <a href="/architecture/">Walk through the infrastructure</a> or
        <a href="/catalog/">browse the catalog</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>

  <style>
    .doc { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; padding: clamp(48px, 8vw, 96px) clamp(24px, 6vw, 48px); }
    .doc__head { margin-bottom: 8vh; }
    .doc__kicker {
      font-family: 'Apex Mk3', 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--misc-accent, #5061b9);
      margin: 0 0 20px;
    }
    .doc__title {
      font-family: 'Apex Mk3', sans-serif;
      font-weight: 300;
      font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.6rem);
      line-height: 1;
      margin: 0 0 24px;
      text-transform: lowercase;
    }
    .doc__lede {
      font-family: 'Branding Pro', sans-serif;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.55;
      color: var(--misc-ink-soft, #6b6b6b);
      margin: 0;
      max-width: 620px;
    }
    .sec { margin-bottom: 8vh; }
    .sec__num {
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      color: var(--misc-accent, #5061b9);
      margin: 0 0 6px;
    }
    .sec__h {
      font-family: 'Apex Mk3', sans-serif;
      font-weight: 400;
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      color: var(--misc-ink, #1a1a1a);
      margin: 0 0 20px;
      padding-bottom: 12px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--misc-line, rgba(0,0,0,0.14));
      text-transform: lowercase;
    }
    .sec__sub {
      font-family: 'Apex Mk3', sans-serif;
      font-weight: 400;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--misc-ink);
      margin: 32px 0 12px;
      text-transform: lowercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    }
    .sec p, .sec li { font-family: 'Branding Pro', sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 16px; color: var(--misc-ink); }
    .grid { display: grid; gap: 20px; margin-top: 20px; }
    .grid--2 { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .face {
      padding: 20px;
      background: #fff;
      border: 1px solid var(--misc-line, rgba(0,0,0,0.14));
      clip-path: polygon(0 0, calc(100% - 10px) 0, 100% 10px, 100% 100%, 0 100%);
    }
    .face__name {
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 0.68rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--misc-accent, #5061b9);
      margin: 0 0 10px;
    }
    .face__role { font-size: 0.9rem; margin: 0; color: var(--misc-ink-soft); }
    .face__sample { font-size: 1.5rem; margin: 4px 0 14px; line-height: 1.1; color: var(--misc-ink); }
    .swatches { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(160px, 1fr)); gap: 12px; margin-top: 12px; }
    .sw { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--misc-ink-soft); }
    .sw span { display: inline-block; width: 26px; height: 26px; border: 1px solid var(--misc-line); }
    .sec--cta { padding: 28px; background: rgba(80, 97, 185, 0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(80,97,185,0.14); clip-path: polygon(0 0, calc(100% - 14px) 0, 100% 14px, 100% 100%, 0 100%); }
    .sec__cta-kicker {
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      color: var(--misc-accent);
      margin: 0 0 8px;
    }
    .sec__cta-h { font-family: 'Apex Mk3', sans-serif; font-size: 1.6rem; margin: 0 0 12px; font-weight: 300; text-transform: lowercase; }
    .sec--cta p { margin: 0; }
    .sec--cta a { color: var(--misc-accent); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
    @media (max-width: 700px) {
      .grid--2 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
  </style>
</Base>
